<paragraph blockId="46.[733,1328,603,1028]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[736,891,603,636]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Poljakov, 1881" authorityName="Poljakov" authorityYear="1881" box="[905,1318,603,636]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Arvicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddei">Arvicola raddei Poljakov, 1881</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation box="[736,1319,642,675]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">Zun-Torey Lake, Zabaykalsky Krai, Russia.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[733,1328,603,1028]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicName box="[737,999,681,714]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Lasiopodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddei">Lasiopodomys raddei</taxonomicName>
1s in subgenus Stenocranius. In the past, it was considered a welldifferentiated subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1779" box="[1174,1320,761,794]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gregalis">L. gregalis</taxonomicName>
. Specific status was validated with genetic data and experimental hybridization trials with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1779" box="[858,993,879,912]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gregalis">L. gregalis</taxonomicName>
. The genetically dated specimens from Mongolia originate from a single location in the middle Uldza River valley. 
<taxonomicName box="[828,1092,995,1028]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Lasiopodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddei">Lasiopodomys raddei</taxonomicName>
probably occurs
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[117,1326,1039,1815]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">
in Uldza and Onon river basins, with exception of the right bank of lower Uldza River, where 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1779" box="[214,345,1075,1108]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gregalis">L. gregalis</taxonomicName>
was found. Morphologically and genetically, it is sister species to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1779" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gregalis">L. gregalis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="393" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" targetBox="[632,636,1790,1815]" targetPageId="46">
<paragraph blockId="46.[117,1326,1039,1815]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[120,296,1153,1186]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">Distribution.</emphasis>
S Transbaikalia in Russia (Zabaykalsky Krai, S of Shilka and Ingoda rivers) and NE Mongolia; distributional limits in Mongolia are not clearyet.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="393" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="46.[117,1326,1039,1815]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[120,373,1236,1265]" pageId="46" pageNumber="393">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 95-130 mm, tail 21-37 mm, ear 6-12 mm, hindfoot 15-18 mm; weight 24-54 g. Fur color of head and upperparts of Radde’s Vole is light dull pale gray; back of head and anterior part of back never have longitudinal dark strip; underparts are whitish gray; and tail is bicolored, pale gray above and whitish below. Sole of foot has six plantar pads. Braincase is narrow. Auditory bullae are relatively small and not inflated. Enamel pattern of molaris like that of the Narrow-headed Vole (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1779" box="[132,272,1467,1500]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gregalis">L. gregalis</taxonomicName>
). Chromosomal complement is not known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
